                      Many shades of life                    A popular modern form of aesthetic expression, photography has the power to capture the imagination and arouse viewers emotions while transcribing the experience of a single moment. Dedicated to teaching students all aspects of this powerful art form, Light amp; Shadow has nurtured many talents who are currently engaged in the fields of photo-journalism, fashion and advertising. Its ongoing second annual exhibition of photographs comprises 90 works by its students. Featuring images on a diverse array of themes including travel, photo-journalism, studio, creative still-life, figure study, portrait, industrial, purely commercial and conceptual still-life, it aims to make us conscious of the various moods and colours of life that often elude our perception though we may encounter them everyday. Participants: Aniruddha Mitra, Avijit Singha, Chandrajit Chatterjee, Deepsubhro Ghosh, Gopal Chandra Dey, Joydeep Ghosh, Kakoli Dutta, Nupur Sen, Parimal Chakraborty, Payel Chowdhury, Rajat Banerje, Sujoy Biswas, Subir Das, Shivaji Ghosh, Syed Mohsin Reza, Subhasish Banerjee and Tamal Chakraborty.                  Event: Exhibition of photographs by Light amp; Shadow When: Till June 21; 2 pm - 8 pm Where: Gaganendra Shilpa Pradarshashala	                    
